### User Validation API Tests
### Base URL: http://localhost:9090

### Variables for reusable values
@baseUrl = http://localhost:9090
@testUserId = 1
@existingUsername = testuser2024
@existingEmail = testuser@example.com
@validPassword = securepassword123

###
### 1. Check if username is available (new username - should be available)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/check-username/newusername2024
Accept: application/json

###
### 2. Check if username is available (existing username - should be taken)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/check-username/{{existingUsername}}
Accept: application/json

###
### 3. Check username availability with special characters
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/check-username/user_with_underscore
Accept: application/json

###
### 4. Check username availability with numbers
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/check-username/user12345
Accept: application/json

###
### 5. Check username availability (short username)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/check-username/ab
Accept: application/json

###
### 6. Check username availability (long username)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/check-username/thisisaverylongusernamethatexceedsusuallengthlimits
Accept: application/json

###
### 7. Check if email is available (new email - should be available)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/check-email/newemail@example.com
Accept: application/json

###
### 8. Check if email is available (existing email - should be taken)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/check-email/{{existingEmail}}
Accept: application/json

###
### 9. Check email availability with different domains
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/check-email/user@gmail.com
Accept: application/json

###
### 10. Check email availability with subdomain
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/check-email/user@mail.google.com
Accept: application/json

###
### 11. Check email availability with plus addressing
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/check-email/user+test@example.com
Accept: application/json

###
### 12. Check email availability with dots in local part
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/check-email/user.name@example.com
Accept: application/json

###
### 13. Verify password for existing user (correct password)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/{{testUserId}}/check-password?password={{validPassword}}
Accept: application/json

###
### 14. Verify password for existing user (incorrect password)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/{{testUserId}}/check-password?password=wrongpassword123
Accept: application/json

###
### 15. Verify email for existing user (correct email)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/{{testUserId}}/check-email?email={{existingEmail}}
Accept: application/json

###
### 16. Verify email for existing user (incorrect email)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/{{testUserId}}/check-email?email=wrong@example.com
Accept: application/json

###
### 17. Check password for non-existent user (should handle gracefully)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/999/check-password?password=anypassword
Accept: application/json

###
### 18. Check email for non-existent user (should handle gracefully)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/999/check-email?email=any@example.com
Accept: application/json

###
### 19. Check username availability with case variations
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/check-username/TestUser2024
Accept: application/json

###
### 20. Check email availability with case variations
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/check-email/TestUser@Example.Com
Accept: application/json

###
### 21. Check username availability with URL encoding needed
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/check-username/user%40symbol
Accept: application/json

###
### 22. Check empty password (should handle edge case)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/{{testUserId}}/check-password?password=
Accept: application/json